Package software.leonov.common.collect

Interfaces, implementations, and utilities for working with Collections, Iterables, and Iterators.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BoundedMap<K,​V>
    A capacity restricted Map.
    BoundedQueue<E>
    A capacity restricted Queue.
    SortedCollection<E>
    A Collection which maintains its elements in sorted order.
    Sortedlist<E>
    A SortedCollection which may contain duplicate elements and allows users to access or remove elements by their integer index.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Collect
    Static utility methods for working with Collections.
    EquivalenceMap<K,​V>
    A Map implementation which has a predictable iteration order, and allows users to specify their own strategy for comparing keys by providing an Equivalence.
    Iteration
    Static utility methods for working with Iterables and Iterators
    LRUCache<K,​V>
    A special LinkedHashMap which has a maximum size and whose iteration order is the order in which its entries were last accessed, from least-recently to most-recently.
    MoreArrays
    Static utility methods which operate on or return arrays.
    MoreLists
    More static utility methods which operate on or return Lists.
    MoreMaps
    Static utility methods for working with Maps.
    MoreQueues
    More static utility methods which operate on or return Queues.
    RankList<E>
    A List optimized for efficient random access insertion and removal operations.
    Skiplist<E>
    A Sortedlist implementation based on a modified skip list.
    Skiplist.Builder<B>
    A builder for the creation of Skiplist instances.
    SkiplistSet<E> Deprecated.
    This class should only be used for testing.
    TreeBasedSet<E> Deprecated.
    This class should only be used for testing.
    Treelist<E>
    A Sortedlist implementation, based on a modified Red-Black Tree.
    Treelist.Builder<B>
    A builder for the creation of Treelist instances.
    TreeQueue<E>
    An optionally bounded priority Queue based on a modified Red-Black Tree.
    TreeQueue.Builder<B>
    A builder for the creation of TreeQueue instances.
    UnmodifiablePeekingIterator<E>
    A peeking iterator that does not support remove().
